{
  "texts": [
    "Studies 3a and 3b tested the potential of AI-generated matching effects under more conservative conditions to better support our findings' real-world applicability.",
    "This included: (1) replacing the bi-polar response scales with single message evaluations (akin to users scrolling down their newsfeed and evaluating one ad at a time), and (2) gauging message effectiveness on people's willingness-to-pay (WTP; i.e., \"How much would you be willing to spend on X?\")",
    "as a proxy for behavior.",
    "Previous research has found that self-reported WTP is both an interpretable outcome 66 and a reflection of people's actual, in-market demand and pricing decisions 67.",
    "Study 3c complements Studies 3a-b with an experimental between-subjects design in which participants only evaluated one message at a time (instead of a within-subjects design in which participants evaluated all messages)."
  ]
}